claim: The Greenland shark has an external ear.
premise_source_doc_sentence: Otoplasty  (  Greek οὖς , oûs , `` ear '' + πλάσσω plássein , `` to shape ''  )  denotes the surgical and non-surgical procedures for correcting the deformities and defects of the pinna  (  external ear  )  , and for reconstructing a defective , or deformed , or absent external ear , consequent to congenital conditions  (  e.g. microtia , anotia , etc.  )  and trauma  (  blunt , penetrating , or blast  )  .
